      ],
      [
        'Cylinder Manipulation, XHand',
        'xhand_sim_video-720p/dexterhand-Cylinder_00-fps_20-xarm7_xhand-3600_3700-render-720p.mp4'
      ],
      [
        'Cylinder Manipulation, Sharpa',
        'sharpa_sim_video-720p/dexterhand-Cylinder_00-fps_20-rby1a_sharpa-3600_3700-render-720p.mp4'
      ],
      [
        'Ring Manipulation, XHand',
        'xhand_sim_video-720p/dexterhand-Ring_00-fps_20-xarm7_xhand-10240_10340-render-720p.mp4'
      ],
      [
        'Ring Manipulation, Sharpa',
        'sharpa_sim_video-720p/dexterhand-Ring_00-fps_20-rby1a_sharpa-10240_10340-render-720p.mp4'
      ]
    ]
  }
]

const realVideos = [
  [
    'Cylinder Handover, real XHand',
    'real-8x-sdr-720p/grab-s1_cylindermedium_offhand_1-xarm7_xhand-268_628_8x_sdr-720p.mp4'
  ],
  [
    'Hammer Use, real XHand',
    'real-8x-sdr-720p/grab-s1_hammer_use_1-xarm7_xhand-120_840_8x_sdr-720p.mp4'
  ],
  [
    'Cube Manipulation, real XHand',
    'real-8x-sdr-720p/grab-s2_cubemedium_inspect_1-xarm7_xhand-192_672_8x_sdr-720p.mp4'
  ]
]

const bibtex = `@misc{liang2026contrack,
      title={ConTrack: Constrained Hand Motion Tracking with Adaptive Trade-off Control}, 
      author={Liang, Yutong and Peng, Quanquan and Qiu, Ri-Zhao and Wang, Xiaolong},
      year={2026},
      eprint={xxxx.xxxxx},
      archivePrefix={arXiv},
      primaryClass={cs.RO},
      url={https://arxiv.org/abs/xxxx.xxxxx}, 
}`

const approachIntro =
  'ConTrack trains one tracking policy per clip, and the same recipe runs on all of them. It reframes what the robot has to match, controls the resulting trade-off on the fly, restarts training where the policy can actually learn, and borrows contact from the human hand to keep the motion natural.'

const approachSteps = [
  {
    title: 'Track the object, leave the hand free',
    text: 'Each clip gives a sequence of object poses to reproduce, plus a human hand trajectory retargeted onto the robot. Reproducing the object poses is the task; matching the hand is only style. Since an exact hand match is what breaks contact, ConTrack keeps object tracking as a hard constraint and lets hand fidelity go whenever the two conflict.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Adapt the task-style trade-off online',
    text: 'Task and style can rarely both be perfect, and how hard they compete shifts from clip to clip and even within a single clip, so a fixed reward weighting is fragile. ConTrack adjusts the balance during training with one scalar controller. A target ratio alpha sets how much tracking quality the policy must hold, measured against the best tracking it has reached on that clip so far. After each batch of rollouts the controller checks current tracking against this target: when it falls short, weight on the object reward goes up; once it recovers, weight shifts back toward the hand. The same loop runs on every clip, with no per-clip reward tuning.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Reset near failures, then walk back to the start',
    text: 'Even with the trade-off handled, clips are long, and a policy that always restarts from the first frame keeps failing early and never reaches the later contacts to practice them. ConTrack keeps a library of restart states indexed by frame and resets from points where the policy recently failed, so it masters short segments near the edge of its reach first. As these segments improve, the reset distribution moves earlier, until training again covers the clip from the start.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Borrow contact from the human hand',
    text: 'With the hand relaxed and resets pulling training through the hard segments, the object becomes easy to track, but many different robot motions can carry it along the same path and some barely touch it. To pick a natural, contact-rich one, ConTrack reuses the demonstration’s contact labels, which mark which hand link touches the object and where on its surface. The style reward encourages the same links to make contact at the same moments and, when they do touch, pulls the contact toward the labelled point. This recovers the demonstrated grip out of the many that move the object equally well, without ever copying the full hand pose.'
  }
]
---

<html lang='en-US'>
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title='ConTrack'
      description={description}
      canonical='/projects/ConTrack'
      ogImage={teaserImage.src}
    />
    <ThemeProvider />
  </head>
  <body class='contrack-body'>
    <main class='page'>
      <header class='hero'>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class='authors'>
          {
            authors.map((author, index) => (
              <>
                <a
                  href={author.href}
                  class='text-foreground no-underline transition-colors hover:text-primary hover:no-underline'
                  target={author.href === '#' ? undefined : '_blank'}
                  rel={author.href === '#' ? undefined : 'noopener noreferrer'}
                >
                  {author.name}
                </a>
                {index < authors.length - 1 && <span>, </span>}
              </>
            ))
          }
        </p>
        <p class='affiliations'>University of California San Diego</p>
        <div class='links'>
          {
            links.map((link) => (
              <Button
                title={link.label}
                href={link.href}
                style='pill'
                class='px-3 py-1.5 text-base'
                target={link.href === '#' ? undefined : '_blank'}
                rel={link.href === '#' ? undefined : 'noopener noreferrer'}
              />
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </header>

      <figure class='teaser'>
        <img src={teaserImage.src} alt='ConTrack overview teaser.' />
      </figure>

      <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>{overviewIntro}</p>
        <ul class='overview-list'>
          {overviewPoints.map((point) => <li>{point}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Video</h2>
        <iframe
          class='main-video'
          src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/Rr96tHf0ZUU'
          title='ConTrack video'
          allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
          allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Method</h2>
        <p>{approachIntro}</p>
        <ul class='method-steps'>
          {
            approachSteps.map((step) => (
              <li>
                <div>
                  <strong>{step.title}</strong>
                  <span>{step.text}</span>
                </div>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Experiment</h2>
        <p>
          We test ConTrack on bimanual object manipulation (GRAB), articulated tool use (ARCTIC),
          and in-hand rotation (DexterHand). Each video below is one policy per clip, trained with
          the same recipe and shown on both the XHand and Sharpa robot hands.
        </p>

        <h3>Simulation Videos</h3>
        {
          simGroups.map((group) => (
            <div class='sim-group'>
              <h4>{group.name}</h4>
              <div class='video-grid'>
                {group.videos.map(([name, src]) => (
                  <figure>
                    <video
                      class='lazy-video'
                      muted
                      loop
                      playsinline
                      autoplay
                      preload='none'
                      data-src={`${cdn}${src}`}
                    />
                    <figcaption>{name}</figcaption>
                  </figure>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }

        <h3>Real Robot Videos</h3>
        <div class='real-grid'>
          {
            realVideos.map(([name, src]) => (
              <figure>
                <video
                  class='lazy-video'
                  muted
                  loop
                  playsinline
                  autoplay
                  preload='none'
                  data-src={`${cdn}${src}`}
                />
                <figcaption>{name}</figcaption>
              </figure>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>BibTeX</h2>
        <pre><code>{bibtex}</code></pre>
      </section>
    </main>
    <script>
      const videos = [...document.querySelectorAll('video.lazy-video')] as HTMLVideoElement[]
      const loadVideo = (video: HTMLVideoElement) => {
        const src = video.dataset.src
        if (!src || video.src) return
        video.preload = 'auto'
        video.src = src
        video.load()
        video.play().catch(() => {})
      }

      const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            const video = entry.target as HTMLVideoElement
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              loadVideo(video)
              video.play().catch(() => {})
            } else {
              video.pause()
            }
          })
        },
        { rootMargin: '360px 0px', threshold: 0.08 }
      )

      videos.forEach((video) => observer.observe(video))
    </script>
    <Analytics />
    <SpeedInsights />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :global(body.contrack-body) {
    --contrack-bg: #fff;
    --contrack-text: #111;
    --contrack-muted: #555;
    --contrack-line: #ddd;
    --contrack-code-bg: #f7f7f7;
    --contrack-video-bg: #000;
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--contrack-bg);
    color: var(--contrack-text);
  }

  :global(html.dark body.contrack-body) {
    --contrack-bg: #0b0b10;
    --contrack-text: #e8e8ee;
    --contrack-muted: #a6a6b3;
    --contrack-line: #31313a;
    --contrack-code-bg: #17171f;
  }

  .page {
    width: min(980px, calc(100% - 32px));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 0 72px;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.62;
  }

  .hero {
    text-align: center;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 18px;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .authors,
  .affiliations,
  .links {
    margin: 6px 0;
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .authors {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
  }

  .affiliations,
  .muted {
    color: var(--contrack-muted);
  }

  .teaser {
    margin: 34px 0 46px;
  }

  .teaser img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
  }

  section {
    margin-top: 52px;
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--contrack-line);
    padding-bottom: 6px;
    font-size: 1.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  h3 {
    margin: 30px 0 10px;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  h4 {
    margin: 18px 0 10px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .overview-list {
    margin: 8px 0 0;
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .overview-list li {
    position: relative;
    margin: 8px 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .overview-list li::before {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0.72em;
    left: 0;
    width: 0.34rem;
    height: 0.34rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--contrack-text);
    content: '';
  }

  video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--contrack-video-bg);
  }

  .main-video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    border: 0;
    background: var(--contrack-video-bg);
  }

  .method-steps {
    display: grid;
    gap: 14px;
    margin: 6px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .method-steps li {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--contrack-line);
    padding-top: 14px;
  }

  .method-steps li:first-child {
    border-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .method-steps strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .method-steps span {
    display: block;
    color: var(--contrack-text);
  }

  strong {
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .sim-group {
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .video-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .real-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .real-grid figure {
    width: calc((100% - 3 * 12px) / 4);
  }

  figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .video-grid video,
  .real-grid video {
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 5px;
    color: var(--contrack-muted);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  pre {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--contrack-code-bg);
    padding: 14px 16px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .video-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .real-grid figure {
      width: calc((100% - 12px) / 2);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .page {
      width: min(100% - 24px, 980px);
      padding-top: 32px;
    }
  }
</style>
